# Stack

**React Query** (`@tanstack/react-query`) in components. **Axios** only in the API layer — never imported in components/pages.

# Layering

```
components/pages  →  React Query hooks  →  API functions  →  Axios client
```

| Layer | Location | Allowed |
|-------|----------|---------|
| Axios instance | `src/lib/api/client.ts` | Axios config, interceptors, base URL |
| API functions | `src/lib/api/<domain>.ts` | Axios calls only (`api.get`, `api.post`, …) |
| Query hooks | `src/hooks/queries/` | `useQuery`, `useMutation`, `useQueryClient` |
| Components | `src/components/`, `src/pages/` | Query hooks only — **no Axios, no fetch** |

```ts
// src/lib/api/client.ts
import axios from "axios";

export const api = axios.create({
  baseURL: import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL,
});
```

```ts
// src/lib/api/users.ts
import { api } from "./client";
export const getUsers = () => api.get<User[]>("/users").then((r) => r.data);
```

```ts
// src/hooks/queries/useUsers.ts
import { useQuery } from "@tanstack/react-query";
import { getUsers } from "@/lib/api/users";

export function useUsers() {
  return useQuery({ queryKey: ["users"], queryFn: getUsers });
}
```

```tsx
// component — hooks only
const { data, isLoading, isError } = useUsers();
```

- Endpoints → `src/utils/constants.ts`. Env → `VITE_*` only. Type all shapes; no `any`.
- Mutations: `useMutation` in `src/hooks/queries/`, invalidate related keys on success.

# Loading & Empty States

| State | Use |
|-------|-----|
| Loading | `isLoading` / `isPending` → `LoadingStates` skeletons or `ButtonSpinner` |
| Empty / error | `EmptyState` (`variant="error"` for errors) |

Components read query state (`isLoading`, `isError`, `data`) — never manage fetch logic themselves.
